{"questionId": "e4f2c33b-9282-40a7-810c-d633e5197f95_17", "correctAnswer": "A", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Factor out the common factor", "content": "Pull out $p^{17}$: $$49p^{19}-121p^{17}=p^{17}(49p^2-121).$$"}, {"title": "Apply difference of squares", "content": "Then $49p^2-121=(7p-11)(7p+11)$."}, {"title": "Identify the matching factor", "content": "So $7p+11$ is a factor. That matches choice <strong>A</strong> — <strong>A</strong> is correct."}]}